/* [wxMaxima: comment start ]
Therefore x is now ω/k at t 
Therefore kx-wt means that one point on the pulse will move right with increasing time
This applies to all functions of space and time, but is used mainly with harmonic wave equations

Dimensionally this works out to meters

                 ω (radians/s)
time (s) x -------------------------------  s x rad/s = rad, rad/rad = 1, 1/1/meter = meter, then x is in meters
                 k (radians/meter)

Maxima loses some solutions but we only need the real one here anyways.
   [wxMaxima: comment end   ] */


